<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12293] Tests are logging too much</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12293</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In trying to solve &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12285&quot; title=&quot;Builds are failing, possibly because of SUREFIRE-1091&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12285&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12285&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it was pointed out that tests are writing too much to output again. At best, this is a sloppy practice and, at worst, it leaves us open to builds breaking when our test tools can&apos;t handle the flood. If &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nkeywal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nkeywal&quot;&gt;Nicolas Liochon&lt;/a&gt; would be willing give me a little bit of mentoring on how he dealt with this problem a few years back, I&apos;d be happy to add it to my plate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12749122">HBASE-12293</key>
            <summary>Tests are logging too much</summary>
